
Before installing A10 Control, review the deployment options, platform support, and minimum system requirements to ensure a smooth setup and reliable performance.

Deployment Options

A10 Control supports two deployment variants:

A10 Control Lite

Designed for small environments.

Supports ADC and ADO deployments.

Standalone deployment only.

Recommended for managing up to 10 ADC or 5 ADO/TPS devices.

A10 Control Standard

Designed for large enterprises and service providers.

Supports high availability and large-scale deployments.

Supports standalone and 3-node cluster deployments.

Suitable for managing ADC, CGN, ADO, SSLi, and GiFW services.

Supported Platforms

VMware ESXi 8.0 or later

KVM (Red Hat 9.3 or later)

Note: UEFI firmware and NTP configuration are recommended.

Minimum System Requirements
Deployment Type	CPU	Memory	Disk	Devices
A10 Control Lite	16 cores	64 GB RAM	700 GB SSD	1
A10 Control Standard	32 cores	128 GB RAM	700 GB SSD	1

Note: These values are intended for testing and evaluation only, not for production use.

Network Interface Requirements

A10 Control uses two types of interfaces:

Management: For device communication

Data: For analytics data transfer

Standalone deployments require 1 or 2 interfaces, depending on device type.

Multi-node deployments require separate management and data interfaces with floating IPs for high availability.
